---
name: loadable
version: 1.2.0

title: Loadable
summary: Safely Customize Ruby's Load System
created: 2010-07-21

description:
  Loadable modifieds Ruby's load/require system
  to handle "load wedges", which work much like
  routes in web frameworks, but in this case
  determine which files get loaded.

authors: 
  - Thomas Sawyer <transfire@gmail.com>

requirements:
  - detroit  (build)
  - minitest (test)
  - minitap  (test)
  - rake     (build)

resources:
  home: http://rubyworks.github.com/loadable
  code: http://github.com/rubyworks/loadable

repositories:
  upstream: git://github.com/rubyworks/loadable.git

